parameters.description:
From 040.RC

Range Check
0 Default
1 Range Check passed,CPR Validation pending

Indicates that the position reported by the target is within a
credible range from the ground station. The range check is followed
by the CPR validation to ensure that global and local position
decoding both indicate valid position information. Bit 3=1 indicates
that the range check was done, but the CPR validation is not yet
completed.
Once CPR validation is completed, Bit 3 will be reset to 0.
parameters.name: Range Check Passed

parameters.description:
From 040.RCF

Range Check
0 default
1 Range Check failed

Indicates that the Range Check failed, i.e. the target is
reported outside the credible range for the Ground Station. For
operational users such a target will be suppressed. In services
used for monitoring the Ground Station, the target will be
transmitted with bit 2 indicating the fault condition.
parameters.name: Range Check Failed

by the ground station, expressed as fraction of the second of the
UTC Time.
